HEADWORD: Mysticete
<hw>Mys"ti*cete</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>my`stax</grk> the upper lip, also, the mustache + <grk>kh^tos</grk>
a whale.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any right whale, or whalebone
whale. See <er>Cetacea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

